				<td class="PanelBodyAlternate"><span class="SmallBoldText">Re: Anyone else encountering this issue?<a name="3388"/></span><br><span class="SmallText"> Posted: </span><span class="SmallText">Jan 21 03 3:23 PM</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span>There is another thread around here that deals partially with the issue of using macros to twist multiple songs during combat. It was brought up that using multiple song macros was not efficient due to missed notes, interrupts etc.  That seemed to make sense to me when I read it so I haven't gone further.  I have however, set up practice spell macros to cast a spell 5 times on one hotkey (for my second account cleric I'm PLing) and have macros set up for my cleric to heal and buff me at the touch of a button.
<br />

<br />
My point is, if you, being an uber bard IMHO, have had success in the area of multi song macro twisting, I would like to hear more about it. I know others would benefit from the ability to twist more with less effort. Especially when meleeing, which isn't all that difficult, but any help would be appreciated.  Especially since my guild and group members think I don't know how to type as I never talk while twisting (other than my guild chat hotkeys I've got set up for just about any occasion, ROFL, shh don't tell them).
<br />

<br />
On a related note, being able to use macros could (lag permitting) allow me to potentially twist 4 songs reliably.  I know it's possible as 3 ticks is 18 seconds and it only takes 3 seconds to cast a song, so that's 6 songs you could theoretically get off without having the first song fade.  Yes I know that there are other recast time factors involved, but you get my meaning.  I'd be happy with 4 non-extended-duration songs up at the same time consistently.  I haven't mastered that yet and hope this could help cheat.
<br />

<br />
Thoughts?
<br />

<br />
Sinfonian Barelytone</span></td>
